I manage a $50M portfolio of business and lead a highly experienced team to maximize value for our clients using our technology products and cloud services. Regional Technology Manager - Azure March 2015 - June 2016 (1 year 4 months) Responsible for helping Microsoft's largest customers realize business value through industry solutions based on the azure platform. In this role I cover the full solution cycle including business envisioning, business case development, solution architecture, and successful implementation and adoption. I'm also responsible for identifying organizational, technical, and operational issues that can be addressed to improve Microsoft's effectiveness in servicing its customers. Enterprise Architect January 2014 - March 2015 (1 year 3 months) I work within Microsoft's Enterprise Strategy Practice. The goal of this practice is to help Microsoft's most strategic clients achieve value through successful completion of business transformation oriented projects by using the disciplines of enterprise architecture, portfolio management, business strategy, and value realization. Lead Architect for large global Team for a Tier 1 Investment bank, building an innovative industry-leading interactive market risk management application for the Chief Risk Officer and top 40 Risk officers. 2\. Building a business engagement framework for a global insurance firm to quickly align and plan collaboration and social assets from IT shared services to business objectives for maximum impact. 3\. Defining the business value of collaboration & social for a global insurance firm and leading the adoption & change management planning and execution.
